You tell me abou CMU Serif font ChatGPT CMU Serif is a member of the Computer Modern Unicode (CMU) font family, which was developed as an extended and modernized version of the original Computer Modern fonts designed by Donald Knuth for TeX. Here’s an overview of CMU Serif: Key Features Style & Appearance: CMU Serif is a transitional serif typeface, meaning it has moderate contrast between thick and thin strokes.
